2514/* This routine is to handle sequential array section.
2515 * It will try to find correct retval and descr
2516 * If it is continuous section
2517 * retval = first_array_element,
2518 * descr = new descriptor based on shape
2519 * else it will copy to tmp before and after
2520 * retval = first_element_of_(tmp)
2521 * descr = tmp_descriptor
2522 */
2523static void
2524handle_seq_section(int entry, int arr, int loc, int std, int *retval,
2525 int *descr, LOGICAL stride1, int dummysptr)
2526{
2527 int sec;
2528 int arraysptr;
2529 int arrayalign;
2530 int arrayast;
2531
2532 int topsptr;
2533 int topdtype;
2534 LOGICAL simplewholearray;
2535 LOGICAL is_seq_pointer, is_pointer;
2536 LOGICAL continuous, desc_needed;
2537 int is_hcc;
2538 int iface; /* sptr of explicit interface; could be zero */
2539
2540 /* find a distributed array, if any, and its alignment */
2541 arrayast = arr;
2542 arraysptr = 0;
2543 topsptr = 0;
2544 arrayalign = 0;
2545 is_seq_pointer = FALSE;
2546 is_pointer = FALSE;
2547 simplewholearray = TRUE;
2548 do {
2549 switch (A_TYPEG(arrayast)) {
2550 case A_ID:
2551 arraysptr = A_SPTRG(arrayast);
2552 if (topsptr == 0)
2553 topsptr = arraysptr;
2554 arrayalign = ALIGNG(arraysptr);
2555 if (POINTERG(arraysptr)) {
2556 is_pointer = TRUE;
2557 if (!arrayalign)
2558 is_seq_pointer = TRUE;
2559 }
2560 if (TARGETG(arraysptr) && XBIT(58,0x400000))
2561 is_seq_pointer = TRUE;
2562 /* for F90, an assumed-shape dummy array looks like
2563 * a sequential pointer, if copy-ins are removed */
2564 if (XBIT(57, 0x10000) && ASSUMSHPG(arraysptr) && SDSCS1G(arraysptr) &&
2565 !XBIT(54, 2))
2566 is_seq_pointer = TRUE;
2567 break;
2568 case A_SUBSCR:
2569 arrayast = A_LOPG(arrayast);
2570 simplewholearray = FALSE;
2571 break;
2572 case A_MEM:
2573 arraysptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(arrayast));
2574 if (topsptr == 0)
2575 topsptr = arraysptr;
2576 /* is the array shape from the member or from the parent */
2577 if (A_SHAPEG(A_PARENTG(arrayast))) {
2578 /* parent is array shaped, member should not be */
2579 arraysptr = 0;
2580 arrayast = A_PARENTG(arrayast);
2581 simplewholearray = FALSE;
2582 } else {
2583 /* right now, no members can be distributed anyway */
2584 arrayalign = ALIGNG(arraysptr);
2585 if (POINTERG(arraysptr)) {
2586 is_pointer = TRUE;
2587 if (!arrayalign)
2588 is_seq_pointer = TRUE;
2589 }
2590 }
2591 break;
2592 default:
2593 interr("handle_seq_section: unknown ast", arr, 4);
2594 break;
2595 }
2596 } while (arraysptr == 0);
2597
2598 topdtype = DTYPEG(topsptr);
2599 if (DTY(topdtype) == TY_ARRAY)
2600 topdtype = DTY(topdtype + 1);
2601
2602 if (simplewholearray && !is_pointer && CONTIGATTRG(arraysptr)) {
2603 /* Note: The call to first_element() uses the descriptor of the declared
2604 * dtype of arr which is fine for simple regular arrays. But it does not
2605 * work for pointers since a pointer's descriptor can change depending on
2606 * the pointer target. Typically this is accomplished by creating a section
2607 * descriptor first (i.e., call mk_descr_from_section()) which takes into
2608 * account the runtime shape of the pointer target. We handle this and
2609 * other pointer cases below.
2610 */
2611 *retval = first_element(arr);
2612 *descr = DESCRG(arraysptr) > NOSYM ?
2613 check_member(arrayast, mk_id(DESCRG(arraysptr))) : 0;
2614 return;
2615 }
2616
2617 /* whole array with no distribution */
2618 if (!is_seq_pointer
2619 /* for F90, pointers may not be contiguous */
2620 && !(is_pointer && XBIT(58, 0x10000)) && simplewholearray) {
2621 *retval = arr;
2622 *descr = DESCRG(arraysptr) > NOSYM ? check_member(arrayast, mk_id(DESCRG(arraysptr))) : 0;
2623 return;
2624 }
2625
2626 proc_arginfo(entry, NULL, NULL, &iface);
2627 if (!is_procedure_ptr(entry)) {
2628 is_hcc = HCCSYMG(entry);
2629 } else {
2630 is_hcc = 0;
2631 }
2632
2633 /* undistributed pointer, no alignment, whole array, F90 callee */
2634 if (is_seq_pointer && !XBIT(58, 0x10000) && simplewholearray) {
2635 if (is_hcc || (XBIT(28, 0x10))) {
2636 *retval = arr;
2637 *descr = DESCRG(arraysptr) > NOSYM ? check_member(arrayast, mk_id(DESCRG(arraysptr))) : 0;
2638 return;
2639 }
2640 }
2641 assert(is_array_type(arraysptr), "handle_seq_section: symbol not array",
2642 arraysptr, 3);
2643 arr = convert_subscript(arr);
2644
2645 desc_needed = is_desc_needed(entry, arr, loc);
2646 continuous = continuous_section(entry, arr, loc, 0);
2647
2648 if (is_seq_pointer) {
2649 if (XBIT(58, 0x10000)) {
2650 if (continuous) {
2651 if (CONTIGATTRG(arraysptr)) {
2652 if (!desc_needed) {
2653 *descr = pghpf_type(0);
2654 }
2655 else {
2656 *descr = mk_descr_from_section(arr, topdtype, std);
2657 }
2658 *retval = first_element_from_section(arr);
2659 return;
2660 }
2661 if (!desc_needed)
2662 copy_arg_to_seq_tmp(entry, loc, topdtype, arraysptr, arr, std, retval,
2663 descr, TRUE, stride1, simplewholearray);
2664 else
2665 copy_arg_to_seq_tmp(entry, loc, topdtype, arraysptr, arr, std, retval,
2666 descr, FALSE, stride1, simplewholearray);
2667 } else {
2668 copy_arg_to_seq_tmp(entry, loc, topdtype, arraysptr, arr, std, retval,
2669 descr, FALSE, stride1, simplewholearray);
2670 }
2671 } else {
2672 /* If the formal parameter does not need (allow) a runtime descriptor,
2673 * call copy_arg_to_seq_tmp to determine whether the actual parameter
2674 * should be copied or not. Also, adjust `retval' to refer to the
2675 * first entry if the actual is not the whole array.
2676 *
2677 * Otherwise, insure that the runtime descriptor exists and set `retval'
2678 * to first element of the array (section).
2679 */
2680 if (simplewholearray) {
2681 if (desc_needed) {
2682 /* undistributed whole pointer array */
2683 *retval = arrayast;
2684 *descr = check_member(arrayast, mk_id(DESCRG(arraysptr)));
2685 } else {
2686 copy_arg_to_seq_tmp(entry, loc, topdtype, arraysptr, arr, std, retval,
2687 descr, TRUE, stride1, simplewholearray);
2688 }
2689 } else if (!continuous) {
2690 copy_arg_to_seq_tmp(entry, loc, topdtype, arraysptr, arr, std, retval,
2691 descr, FALSE, stride1, simplewholearray);
2692 } else if (!desc_needed) {
2693 copy_arg_to_seq_tmp(entry, loc, topdtype, arraysptr, arr, std, retval,
2694 descr, TRUE, stride1, simplewholearray);
2695 *retval = first_element_from_section(arr);
2696 } else {
2697 if (SDSCG(arraysptr)) {
2698 int secss, secsptr;
2699 secss = find_section_subscript(arr);
2700 sec = make_sec_from_ast(secss, std, std, 0, 0);
2701 secsptr = sptr_of_subscript(secss);
2702 *retval = check_member(A_LOPG(secss), mk_id(secsptr));
2703 *retval = replace_ast_subtree(arr, secss, *retval);
2704 *descr = check_member(A_LOPG(secss), mk_id(sec));
2705 } else {
2706 *descr = mk_descr_from_section(arr, topdtype, std);
2707 *retval = first_element_from_section(arr);
2708 }
2709 }
2710 }
2711 return;
2712 }
2713
2714 /* f90 language */
2715 if (!desc_needed && (!continuous || (is_pointer && XBIT(58, 0x10000)))) {
2716 copy_arg_to_seq_tmp(entry, loc, topdtype, arraysptr, arr, std, retval,
2717 descr, FALSE, stride1, simplewholearray);
2718 *descr = pghpf_type(0);
2719 if (!DESCUSEDG(A_SPTRG(*retval)))
2720 NODESCP(A_SPTRG(*retval), 1);
2721 return;
2722 }
2723
2724 if (!desc_needed) {
2725 *descr = pghpf_type(0);
2726 *retval = first_element_from_section(arr);
2727 } else if (continuous && !arrayalign) {
2728 /* unused variable, it just made for new descriptor */
2729 *descr = mk_descr_from_section(arr, topdtype, std);
2730 *retval = first_element_from_section(arr);
2731 } else {
2732 int dd;
2733 dd = dummysptr;
2734 if (!dd) {
2735 /*
2736 * Would have liked to have set dummysptr, but its purpose for
2737 * error checking and when/where is determined by the context
2738 * of calling handle_seq_section() ... in my situation, I'm
2739 * trying to capture an array section where we only know if
2740 * it's contiguous at run-time - the REFLECTED check below is
2741 * invalid when the actual argument is an array section ....
2742 */
2743 dd = find_dummy(entry, loc);
2744 }
2745 if ( dd && ASSUMSHPG(dd) &&
2746 (ignore_tkr(dd, IGNORE_C) ||
2747 (XBIT(58, 0x400000) && TARGETG(dd)))) {
2748 int secss, secsptr;
2749 secss = find_section_subscript(arr);
2750 if (XBIT(57, 0x200000)) {
2751 sec = make_sec_from_ast_chk(secss, std, std, 0, SECTZBASE, 1);
2752 *retval = first_element_from_section(arr);
2753 } else {
2754 /*
2755 * WE want the beginning of the array rather than the first
2756 * element:
2757 */
2758 sec = make_sec_from_ast_chk(secss, std, std, 0, 0, 1);
2759 secsptr = sptr_of_subscript(secss);
2760 *retval = check_member(A_LOPG(secss), mk_id(secsptr));
2761 *retval = replace_ast_subtree(arr, secss, *retval);
2762 }
2763 *descr = check_member(A_LOPG(secss), mk_id(sec));
2764 return;
2765 }
2766 copy_arg_to_seq_tmp(entry, loc, topdtype, arraysptr, arr, std, retval,
2767 descr, FALSE, stride1, simplewholearray);
2768 }
2769}
2770
2771static int
2772mk_descr_from_section(int section, DTYPE topdtype, int std)
2773{
2774 int tmp;
2775 int subscr[MAXDIMS];
2776 tmp = mk_shape_sptr(A_SHAPEG(section), subscr, topdtype);
2777 DESCUSEDP(tmp, 1);
2778 NODESCP(tmp, 0);
2779 emit_alnd_secd(tmp, 0, TRUE, std, 0);
2780 return mk_id(INS_DESCR(SECDG(DESCRG(tmp))));
2781}

2783/*
2784 * is this a small-constant shape?
2785 */
2786static int
2787small_shape(int shd)
2788{
2789 int ndim, i, astlw, astup, aststride;
2790 ISZ_T size, lw, up, stride;
2791 ndim = SHD_NDIM(shd);
2792 size = 1;
2793 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
2794 if (!A_ALIASG(SHD_LWB(shd, i)))
2795 return 0;
2796 if (!A_ALIASG(SHD_UPB(shd, i)))
2797 return 0;
2798 if (SHD_STRIDE(shd, i) && !A_ALIASG(SHD_STRIDE(shd, i)))
2799 return 0;
2800 astlw = A_ALIASG(SHD_LWB(shd, i));
2801 lw = ad_val_of(A_SPTRG(astlw));
2802 astup = A_ALIASG(SHD_UPB(shd, i));
2803 up = ad_val_of(A_SPTRG(astup));
2804 stride = 1;
2805 if (SHD_STRIDE(shd, i)) {
2806 aststride = A_ALIASG(SHD_STRIDE(shd, i));
2807 stride = ad_val_of(A_SPTRG(aststride));
2808 }
2809 size *= (up - lw + stride) / stride;
2810 if (size > 20) {
2811 return 0;
2812 }
2813 }
2814 return 1;
2815} /* small_shape */

2817/*
2818 * allocate a temporary array and its pointer
2819 */
2820static int
2821new_seq_temp_array(int shd, int small, int dtype, int cvlen, int oldsptr,
2822 int mustallocate)
2823{
2824 int ndim, i;
2825 int sptr, sptrdtype, ptr, astlw, astup, aststride;
2826
2827 /* determine how many dimensions are needed, and which ones they are */
2828 ndim = SHD_NDIM(shd);
2829 assert(ndim <= MAXDIMS, "new_seq_temp_array: too many dimensions", ndim, 4);
2830 /* get the temporary */
2831 sptr = sym_get_array("tmp", "r", dtype, ndim);
2832 /* make the descriptors for the temporary */
2833 trans_mkdescr(sptr);
2834 /* mark as compiler created */
2835 HCCSYMP(sptr, 1);
2836 if (cvlen) {
2837 CVLENP(sptr, cvlen);
2838 ADJLENP(sptr, 1);
2839 }
2840 if (!ADJLENG(sptr) && !mustallocate && small) {
2841 SCP(sptr, symutl.sc);
2842 /* fill in the bounds */
2843 sptrdtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2844 ADD_MLPYR(sptrdtype, 0) = astb.bnd.one;
2845 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
2846 astlw = A_ALIASG(SHD_LWB(shd, i));
2847 astup = A_ALIASG(SHD_UPB(shd, i));
2848 if (SHD_STRIDE(shd, i)) {
2849 aststride = A_ALIASG(SHD_STRIDE(shd, i));
2850 }
2851 if (aststride == astb.i1 || aststride == astb.bnd.one)
2852 aststride = 0;
2853 ADD_LWBD(sptrdtype, i) = ADD_LWAST(sptrdtype, i) = astb.bnd.one;
2854 astup = mk_binop(OP_SUB, astup, astlw, astb.bnd.dtype);
2855 if (!aststride) {
2856 astup = mk_binop(OP_ADD, astup, astb.bnd.one, astb.bnd.dtype);
2857 } else {
2858 astup = mk_binop(OP_ADD, astup, aststride, astb.bnd.dtype);
2859 astup = mk_binop(OP_DIV, astup, aststride, astb.bnd.dtype);
2860 }
2861 ADD_UPBD(sptrdtype, i) = ADD_UPAST(sptrdtype, i) = astup;
2862 ADD_EXTNTAST(sptrdtype, i) = mk_extent(astb.bnd.one, astup, i);
2863 ADD_MLPYR(sptrdtype, i + 1) =
2864 mk_binop(OP_MUL, ADD_MLPYR(sptrdtype, i), astup, astb.bnd.dtype);
2865 ALLOCP(sptr, 0);
2866 }
2867 } else {
2868 /* make it allocatable */
2869 ptr = get_next_sym(SYMNAME(sptr), "p");
2870 STYPEP(ptr, ST_VAR);
2871 SCP(ptr, symutl.sc);
2872 DTYPEP(ptr, DT_PTR);
2873 DCLDP(ptr, 0);
2874 SCP(sptr, SC_BASED);
2875 MIDNUMP(sptr, ptr);
2876 ALLOCP(sptr, 1);
2877 }
2878 return sptr;
2879} /* new_seq_temp_array */
2880
2881#define TEMP_AREA 6
2882
2883typedef struct T_LIST {
2884 struct T_LIST *next;
2885 int temp, shd, dtype, cvlen, std, sc;
2886} T_LIST;
2887
2888#define GET_T_LIST(q) q = (T_LIST *)getitem(TEMP_AREA, sizeof(T_LIST))
2889static T_LIST *templist;
2890
2891/*
2892 * try to reuse an old temp array
2893 * the goal here is to create fewer temp arrays and fewer descriptors,
2894 * so the frame size doesn't get too big
2895 */
2896static int
2897make_seq_temp_array(int shd, int dtype, int oldsptr, int mustallocate, int std)
2898{
2899 int sptr, small, cvlen, ndim, i;
2900 T_LIST *q;
2901 small = small_shape(shd);
2902 cvlen = 0;
2903 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR && ADJLENG(oldsptr) && !F90POINTERG(oldsptr)) {
2904 cvlen = CVLENG(oldsptr);
2905 small = 0;
2906 }
2907 ndim = SHD_NDIM(shd);
2908 for (q = templist; q; q = q->next) {
2909 if (q->std == std || q->dtype != dtype || q->cvlen != cvlen ||
2910 q->sc != symutl.sc)
2911 continue;
2912 if (ndim != SHD_NDIM(q->shd))
2913 continue;
2914 /* see if this is allocatable */
2915 if (mustallocate || !small) {
2916 if (!ALLOCG(q->temp))
2917 continue;
2918 } else {
2919 /* must have the right fixed shape */
2920 if (ALLOCG(q->temp))
2921 continue;
2922 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
2923 if (SHD_LWB(shd, i) != SHD_LWB(q->shd, i) ||
2924 SHD_UPB(shd, i) != SHD_UPB(q->shd, i) ||
2925 SHD_STRIDE(shd, i) != SHD_STRIDE(q->shd, i))
2926 break;
2927 }
2928 if (i < ndim)
2929 continue;
2930 }
2931 q->std = std;
2932 return q->temp;
2933 }
2934 /* see if we have a temp array that will fill the bill */
2935 sptr = new_seq_temp_array(shd, small, dtype, cvlen, oldsptr, mustallocate);
2936 GET_T_LIST(q);
2937 q->next = templist;
2938 templist = q;
2939 q->temp = sptr;
2940 q->shd = shd;
2941 q->dtype = dtype;
2942 q->cvlen = cvlen;
2943 q->std = std;
2944 q->sc = symutl.sc;
2945 return sptr;
2946} /* make_seq_temp_array */
2947
2948/*
2949 * if the section dimension is only the leading dimension, return TRUE
2950 * else, FALSE
2951 */
2952static LOGICAL
2953leading_section(int ast)
2954{
2955 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR) {
2956 int asd, numdim, i, ss;
2957 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
2958 numdim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
2959 for (i = 0; i < numdim; ++i) {
2960 ss = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
2961 if (A_TYPEG(ss) == A_TRIPLE) {
2962 /* triple in any but first dimension is bad */
2963 if (i != 0)
2964 return FALSE;
2965 } else {
2966 /* not having a triple in the first dimension is bad */
2967 if (i == 0)
2968 return FALSE;
2969 /* any dimension having a vector subscript is bad */
2970 if (A_SHAPEG(ss) != 0)
2971 return FALSE;
2972 }
2973 }
2974 /* here, must have a triple in 1st dimension and no others */
2975 return TRUE;
2976 }
2977 return FALSE;
2978} /* leading_section */
2979
2980static void
2981copy_arg_to_seq_tmp(int entry, int loc, int eledtype, int arraysptr,
2982 int arr_ast, int std, int *retval, int *descr,
2983 LOGICAL actual_is_contiguous, LOGICAL stride1,
2984 LOGICAL wholearray)
2985{
2986 int tmp, tmpptr = 0, tmp_id, tmp_ast, array_ptr_ast = 0, iftest = 0, ifast;
2987 int copy_args = 0;

3405int
3406rename_forall_list(int forall)
3407{
3408 int isptr, new_isptr;
3409 int oldast, newast;
3410 int newforall;
3411 int list, listp;
3412
3413 list = A_LISTG(forall);
3414 ast_visit(1, 1);
3415 for (listp = list; listp != 0; listp = ASTLI_NEXT(listp)) {
3416 isptr = ASTLI_SPTR(listp);
3417 new_isptr = sym_get_scalar(SYMNAME(isptr), "i", astb.bnd.dtype);
3418 newast = mk_id(new_isptr);
3419 oldast = mk_id(isptr);
3420 ast_replace(oldast, newast);
3421 }
3422
3423 newforall = ast_rewrite(forall);
3424 ast_unvisit();
3425 A_ARRASNP(newforall, A_ARRASNG(forall));
3426 A_STARTP(newforall, A_STARTG(forall));
3427 A_NCOUNTP(newforall, A_NCOUNTG(forall));
3428 A_CONSTBNDP(newforall, A_CONSTBNDG(forall));
3429
3430 return newforall;
3431}

3433/* This routine is to make array element from array section.
3434 * For example, A(3:20,7:30) will be A(3,7). It only uses lower bounds.
3435 * This routine is used to implement sequence association.
3436 */
3437
3438static int
3439first_element_from_section(int arr)
3440{
3441 ADSC *ad;
3442 int i;
3443 int glb;
3444 int asd;
3445 int triple, lop, parent;
3446 int sptr;
3447 int ndim, numdim;
3448 int newarr;
3449 int subs[MAXDIMS];
3450
3451 switch (A_TYPEG(arr)) {
3452 case A_ID:
3453 return arr;
3454 case A_MEM:
3455 /* do the parent */
3456 parent = first_element_from_section(A_PARENTG(arr));
3457 return mk_member(parent, A_MEMG(arr), A_DTYPEG(A_MEMG(arr)));
3458 case A_SUBSCR:
3459 lop = A_LOPG(arr);
3460 if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_MEM) {
3461 parent = first_element_from_section(A_PARENTG(lop));
3462 lop = mk_member(parent, A_MEMG(lop), A_DTYPEG(A_MEMG(lop)));
3463 A_LOPP(arr, lop);
3464 }
3465 sptr = sptr_of_subscript(arr);
3466 assert(is_array_type(sptr), "first_element_from_section: arg not array", 0,
3467 4);
3468 ndim = rank_of(DTYPEG(sptr));
3469 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
3470 asd = A_ASDG(arr);
3471 numdim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3472 assert(numdim == ndim, "first_element_from_sectio: numdim from ST", sptr,
3473 3);
3474 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
3475 if (A_TYPEG(triple = ASD_SUBS(asd, i)) == A_TRIPLE) {
3476 glb = A_LBDG(triple);
3477 if (glb == 0)
3478 glb = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
3479 if (glb == 0)
3480 glb = mk_isz_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype);
3481 } else {
3482 glb = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
3483 }
3484 subs[i] = glb;
3485 }
3486 newarr = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(arr), subs, ndim, DTY(A_DTYPEG(A_LOPG(arr)) + 1));
3487 return newarr;
3488 default:
3489 interr("first_element_from_section: unknown ast", arr, 4);
3490 return 0;
3491 }
3492}

3494/* assign 'ast' to a temp integer before 'std' */
3495static int
3496tmp_assign(int ast, int std)
3497{
3498 int tmp, tmpast, asn, newstd;
3499 LOGICAL rhs_is_dist = FALSE;
3500 tmp = sym_get_scalar("sub", "a", DT_INT);
3501 /* make assignment to temp_sclr */
3502 asn = mk_stmt(A_ASN, DT_INT);
3503 tmpast = mk_id(tmp);
3504 A_DESTP(asn, tmpast);
3505 A_SRCP(asn, ast);
3506
3507 newstd = add_stmt_before(asn, std);
3508 STD_AST(newstd) = asn;
3509 A_STDP(asn, newstd);

3511 A_SRCP(asn, ast);

3513} /* tmp_assign */
3514
3515/* where 'ast' is the expression we are looking for,
3516 * look at all arguments; if the argument is an array or member,
3517 * look at all scalar subscripts. We don't need to worry about
3518 * vector subscripts, they are handled by creating a section.
3519 * If ast appears in any of the scalar subscripts, remove that
3520 * subscript to a temp */
3521static void
3522remove_from_scalar_subscript(int ast, int argt, int nargs, int std)
3523{
3524 int i, ele, asd, ndim, d, firsttmp;
3525 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
3526 ele = ARGT_ARG(argt, i);
3527 /* look at all scalar subscripts */
3528 firsttmp = 1;
3529 while (ele) {
3530 switch (A_TYPEG(ele)) {
3531 default: /* operators, simple ID, leave alone */
3532 ele = 0;
3533 break;
3534 case A_MEM: /* look for other subscripts */
3535 ele = A_PARENTG(ele);
3536 break;
3537 case A_SUBSCR: /* look for 'ast' in any scalar subscripts */
3538 asd = A_ASDG(ele);
3539 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3540 for (d = 0; d < ndim; ++d) {
3541 int sub;
3542 sub = ASD_SUBS(asd, d);
3543 /* ignore vector subscripts here */
3544 if (A_SHAPEG(sub))
3545 continue;
3546 if (A_TYPEG(sub) == A_TRIPLE)
3547 continue;
3548 /* if already replaced don't need to do it again */
3549 if (A_REPLG(sub))
3550 continue;
3551 if (expr_dependent(sub, ast, std, std)) {
3552 int tmp;
3553 tmp = tmp_assign(sub, std);
3554 SYMLKP(tmp, firsttmp);
3555 firsttmp = tmp;
3556 ADDRESSP(tmp, sub); /* stuff it here */
3557 }
3558 }
3559 /* go to subscript parent */
3560 ele = A_LOPG(ele);
3561 break;
3562 }
3563 }
3564 if (firsttmp > 1) {
3565 int t, nt, sub;
3566 ast_visit(1, 1);
3567 for (t = firsttmp; t > 1; t = nt) {
3568 nt = SYMLKG(t);
3569 SYMLKP(t, 1);
3570 sub = ADDRESSG(t);
3571 ADDRESSP(t, 0);
3572 ast_replace(sub, mk_id(t));
3573 }
3574 ele = ARGT_ARG(argt, i);
3575 ele = ast_rewrite(ele);
3576 ARGT_ARG(argt, i) = ele;
3577 ast_unvisit();
3578 }
3579 }
3580} /* remove_from_scalar_subscript */

3582static void
3583is_function_common(int ast, LOGICAL *any)
3584{
3585 int sptr;
3586 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
3587 case A_FUNC:
3588 *any = TRUE;
3589 break;
3590 case A_ID:
3591 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
3592 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
3593 case ST_VAR:
3594 case ST_ARRAY:
3595 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK) {
3596 *any = TRUE;
3597 }
3598 break;
3599 default:;
3600 }
3601 break;
3602 }
3603} /* is_function_common */
3604
3605static LOGICAL
3606any_functions(int ast)
3607{
3608 LOGICAL any = FALSE;
3609 ast_visit(1, 1);
3610 ast_traverse(ast, NULL, is_function_common, &any);
3611 ast_unvisit();
3612 return any;
3613} /* any_functions */

3615/* look at all arguments; if the argument is an array or member,
3616 * look at all scalar subscripts. We don't need to worry about
3617 * vector subscripts, they are handled by creating a section.
3618 * If a function call or common variable
3619 * appears in any of the scalar subscripts, remove that
3620 * subscript to a temp */
3621static void
3622remove_function_common_from_scalar_subscript(int argt, int nargs, int std)
3623{
3624 int i, ele, asd, ndim, d, firsttmp;
3625 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
3626 ele = ARGT_ARG(argt, i);
3627 /* look at all scalar subscripts */
3628 firsttmp = 1;
3629 while (ele) {
3630 switch (A_TYPEG(ele)) {
3631 default: /* operators, simple ID, leave alone */
3632 ele = 0;
3633 break;
3634 case A_MEM: /* look for other subscripts */
3635 ele = A_PARENTG(ele);
3636 break;
3637 case A_SUBSCR: /* look for 'ast' in any scalar subscripts */
3638 asd = A_ASDG(ele);
3639 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3640 for (d = 0; d < ndim; ++d) {
3641 int sub;
3642 sub = ASD_SUBS(asd, d);
3643 /* ignore vector subscripts here */
3644 if (A_SHAPEG(sub))
3645 continue;
3646 if (A_TYPEG(sub) == A_TRIPLE)
3647 continue;
3648 /* if already replaced don't need to do it again */
3649 if (A_REPLG(sub))
3650 continue;
3651 if (any_functions(sub)) {
3652 int tmp;
3653 tmp = tmp_assign(sub, std);
3654 SYMLKP(tmp, firsttmp);
3655 firsttmp = tmp;
3656 ADDRESSP(tmp, sub); /* stuff it here */
3657 }
3658 }
3659 /* go to subscript parent */
3660 ele = A_LOPG(ele);
3661 break;
3662 }
3663 }
3664 if (firsttmp > 1) {

3667 for (t = firsttmp; t > 1; t = nt) {

3673 }
3674 ele = ARGT_ARG(argt, i);
3675 ele = ast_rewrite(ele);
3676 ARGT_ARG(argt, i) = ele;
3677 ast_unvisit();
3678 }
3679 }
3680} /* remove_function_common_from_scalar_subscript */

3682/* take out scalar arguments if they are used as part of subscript arguments
3683 * For example here: call sub(i,j, a(i,j))
3684 * subroutine may change the value of i and j
3685 */
3686void
3687remove_alias(int std, int ast)
3688{
3689 int argt;
3690 int nargs;
3691 int i;
3692 int ele;
3693
3694 if (pure_gbl.local_mode)
3695 return;
3696 argt = A_ARGSG(ast);
3697 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
3698 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
3699 ele = ARGT_ARG(argt, i);
3700 switch (A_TYPEG(ele)) {
3701 case A_ID:
3702 case A_SUBSCR:
3703 case A_MEM:
3704 break;
3705 default:
3706 continue;
3707 }
3708
3709 /* we have a scalar variable, array element, or member
3710 * see if it is used in the scalar subscript of another argument. */
3711 remove_from_scalar_subscript(ele, argt, nargs, std);
3712 }
3713 /* look for function calls in scalar subscripts, remove them, too. */
3714 remove_function_common_from_scalar_subscript(argt, nargs, std);
3715}

3717static LOGICAL
3718is_desc_needed(int entry, int arr_ast, int loc)
3719{
3720 int iface; /* sptr of explicit interface; could be zero */
3721 int dscptr;
3722 int sptr1;
3723
3724 proc_arginfo(entry, NULL, &dscptr, &iface);
3725
3726 /* only user procedure may not need descr */
3727 if (iface && HCCSYMG(iface))
3728 return TRUE;
3729 if (iface && STYPEG(entry) != ST_PROC && STYPEG(entry) != ST_ENTRY
3730 && (STYPEG(entry) != ST_MEMBER || !VTABLEG(entry)) && !is_procedure_ptr(entry))
3731 return TRUE;
3732 /* for F90, F77, C, need descriptor if copy-in is needed */
3733 if (!dscptr)
3734 return FALSE;
3735 /* sptr = sptr_of_subscript(arr_ast);*/
3736 sptr1 = aux.dpdsc_base[dscptr + loc];
3737 if (sptr1 && is_kopy_in_needed(sptr1))
3738 return TRUE;
3739 /* for F90, need descriptor for assumed-shape arrays */
3740 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr1)) == TY_ARRAY && ASSUMSHPG(sptr1))
3741 return TRUE;
3742 return FALSE;
3743}

3745/*
3746 * Need a copy-out?
3747 * if we know the argument is intent(in), no;
3748 * otherwise, default is yes
3749 */
3750static int
3751need_copyout(int entry, int pos)
3752{
3753 int sptr;
3754 if (HCCSYMG(entry) && INTENTG(entry) == INTENT_IN) {
3755 return 0;
3756 }
3757 sptr = find_dummy(entry, pos);
3758 if (sptr && INTENTG(sptr) == INTENT_IN)
3759 return 0;
3760 return 1;
3761} /* need_copyout */

3763/* Continuous memory rule:
3764 * Trailing dimensions are scalars, preceded by at most one non-full
3765 * dimension (whose stride is 1 and lower bound equal to the dimension's
3766 * lower bound), preceded by full dimensions (a full dimension is a triple
3767 * spanning the dimension's full extent).
3768 * When calling F77_LOCAL, all but the last non-scalar dimension must be
3769 * undistributed.
3770 */
3771static LOGICAL
3772continuous_section(int entry, int arr_ast, int loc, int onlyfirst)
3773{
3774 int asd;
3775 int ndims, dim;
3776 int astsub;
3777 int sptr;
3778
3779 if (!A_SHAPEG(arr_ast))
3780 return TRUE;
3781 asd = A_ASDG(arr_ast);
3782 ndims = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3783
3784 /* Find the 1st non-scalar dimension. */
3785 for (dim = ndims - 1; dim >= 0; dim--)
3786 if (A_TYPEG(ASD_SUBS(asd, dim)) == A_TRIPLE) {
3787 break;
3788 }
3789 if (dim < 0)
3790 return TRUE;
3791 sptr = sym_of_ast(arr_ast);
3792 if (onlyfirst && SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && ASSUMSHPG(sptr) && dim > 0)
3793 return FALSE;
3794 astsub = ASD_SUBS(asd, dim);
3795 if (A_STRIDEG(astsub) && A_STRIDEG(astsub) != astb.i1 &&
3796 A_STRIDEG(astsub) != astb.bnd.one)
3797 return FALSE;
3798
3799 /* Leading dimensions must be full. */
3800 for (--dim; dim >= 0; dim--) {
3801 if (!is_whole_dim(arr_ast, dim))
3802 return FALSE;
3803 }
3804 return TRUE;
3805}
3806
3807/* stride-1 memory rule:
3808 * Leftmost dimension has no stride.
3809 */
3810static LOGICAL
3811stride_1_section(int entry, int arr_ast, int pos, int std)
3812{
3813 int asd;
3814 int ndims, dim;
3815 int astsub, sptr;
3816
3817 if (!A_SHAPEG(arr_ast))
3818 return TRUE;
3819 if (A_TYPEG(arr_ast) == A_SUBSCR) {
3820 asd = A_ASDG(arr_ast);
3821 ndims = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3822
3823 /* Find the 1st non-scalar dimension. */
3824 for (dim = ndims - 1; dim >= 0; --dim) {
3825 if (A_TYPEG(ASD_SUBS(asd, dim)) == A_TRIPLE)
3826 break;
3827 }
3828
3829 if (dim < 0)
3830 return TRUE; /* no triplets */
3831 dim = 0;
3832 astsub = ASD_SUBS(asd, dim);
3833 if (A_TYPEG(astsub) != A_TRIPLE)
3834 return FALSE; /* some triplets, but not in leftmost dimension */
3835 if (A_STRIDEG(astsub) && A_STRIDEG(astsub) != astb.i1 &&
3836 A_STRIDEG(astsub) != astb.k1)
3837 return FALSE; /* leftmost triplet is not stride 1 */
3838 }
3839 sptr = memsym_of_ast(arr_ast);
3840 if (POINTERG(sptr) || (TARGETG(sptr) && XBIT(58,0x400000))) {
3841 /*
3842 * Is this a stride-1 pointer array section? If the corresponding
3843 * dummy is assumed-shape, we cannot omit the copy arg calls. The
3844 * pointer will locate beginning address of the target and the lbase
3845 * of the descriptor can be non-zero; lbase, if non-zero, is the
3846 * distance from the beginning of the target to start of the section.
3847 * Eventually, we'll pass the pointer & descriptor 'as-is'; however,
3848 * we expected the assumed-shape dummmy to correspond to the first
3849 * element of the section. Even if we passed the address of the
3850 * first element, the descriptor's lbase could still be non-zero.
3851 */
3852 int dummy_sptr;
3853 dummy_sptr = find_dummy(entry, pos);
3854 if (dummy_sptr == 0 || !ASSUMSHPG(dummy_sptr)) {
3855 if (pta_stride1(std, sptr)) {
3856 return TRUE;
3857 }
3858 }
3859 return FALSE;
3860 }
3861 return TRUE;
3862} /* stride_1_section */
3863
3864void
3865call_analyze(void)
3866{
3867 int std, stdnext;
3868 int ast;
3869 int parallel_depth;
3870 int task_depth;
3871 int target_depth;
3872
3873 init_region();
3874 parallel_depth = 0;
3875 task_depth = 0;
3876 target_depth = 0;
3877 templist = NULL;
3878 if (flg.opt >= 2 && XBIT(53, 2)) {
3879 points_to();
3880 }
3881 for (std = STD_NEXT(0); std; std = stdnext) {
3882 stdnext = STD_NEXT(std);
3883 gbl.lineno = STD_LINENO(std);
3884 if (STD_PURE(std))
3885 continue;
3886 if (STD_LOCAL(std))
3887 pure_gbl.local_mode = 1; /* don't process for DO-INDEPENDENT */
3888 else
3889 pure_gbl.local_mode = 0;
3890 ast = STD_AST(std);
3891 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
3892 case A_MP_PARALLEL:
3893 ++parallel_depth;
3894 set_descriptor_sc(SC_PRIVATE);
3895 break;
3896 case A_MP_TARGET:
3897 ++target_depth;
3898 set_descriptor_sc(SC_PRIVATE);
3899 break;
3900 case A_MP_ENDPARALLEL:
3901 --parallel_depth;
3902 if (parallel_depth == 0 && task_depth == 0 && target_depth == 0) {
3903 set_descriptor_sc(SC_LOCAL);
3904 }
3905 break;
3906 case A_MP_ENDTARGET:
3907 --target_depth;
3908 if (parallel_depth == 0 && task_depth == 0 && target_depth == 0) {
3909 set_descriptor_sc(SC_LOCAL);
3910 }
3911 break;
3912 case A_MP_TASK:
3913 case A_MP_TASKLOOP:
3914 ++task_depth;
3915 set_descriptor_sc(SC_PRIVATE);
3916 break;
3917 case A_MP_ENDTASK:
3918 case A_MP_ETASKLOOP:
3919 --task_depth;
3920 if (parallel_depth == 0 && task_depth == 0 && target_depth == 0) {
3921 set_descriptor_sc(SC_LOCAL);
3922 }
3923 break;
3924 }
3925 transform_all_call(std, ast);
3926 check_region(std);
3927 }
3928 if (flg.opt >= 2 && XBIT(53, 2)) {
3929 f90_fini_pointsto();
3930 }
3931
3932 freearea(TEMP_AREA);
3933 templist = NULL;
3934}

3936static int
3937transform_all_call(int std, int ast)
3938{
3939 int l, r, d, o;
3940 int l1, l2, l3, l4;
3941 int a;
3942 int astnew, stdnew;
3943 int i, nargs, argt, ag;
3944 int asd;
3945 int ndim;
3946 int subs[MAXDIMS];
3947 int dest;
3948
3949 if (!ast)
3950 return ast;
3951
3952 a = ast;
3953 switch (A_TYPEG(a)) {
3954 /* statements */
3955 case A_ASN:
3956 dest = A_DESTG(a);
3957 dest = transform_all_call(std, A_DESTG(a));
3958 A_DESTP(a, dest);
3959 l = transform_all_call(std, A_SRCG(a));
3960 A_SRCP(a, l);
3961 return a;
3962 case A_IF:
3963 case A_IFTHEN:
3964 /* if there is any copy-in/copy-out code generated,
3965 * it must come BEFORE this statement;
3966 * insert a dummy statement before this one */
3967 astnew = mk_stmt(A_ASN, DT_LOG);
3968 stdnew = add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
3969 l = transform_all_call(stdnew, A_IFEXPRG(a));
3970 if (STD_NEXT(stdnew) == std) {
3971 /* didn't need the new statement, delete it */
3972 STD_PREV(std) = STD_PREV(stdnew);
3973 STD_NEXT(STD_PREV(stdnew)) = std;
3974 STD_PREV(stdnew) = STD_NEXT(stdnew) = 0;
3975 if (astb.std.stg_avail == stdnew + 1) {
3976 /* no statements added, make this one available again */
3977 STG_RETURN(astb.std);
3978 }
3979 A_IFEXPRP(a, l);
3980 } else {
3981 /* have to finish the assignment */
3982 int sptr, asptr;
3983 sptr = sym_get_scalar("if", "tmp", DT_LOG);
3984 asptr = mk_id(sptr);
3985 A_DESTP(astnew, asptr);
3986 A_SRCP(astnew, l);
3987 A_IFEXPRP(a, asptr);
3988 }
3989 return a;
3990
3991 case A_ELSE:
3992 case A_ELSEIF:
3993 case A_ENDIF:
3994 return a;
3995 case A_AIF:
3996 l = transform_all_call(std, A_IFEXPRG(a));
3997 A_IFEXPRP(a, l);
3998 return a;
3999 case A_GOTO:
4000 return a;
4001 case A_CGOTO:
4002 l = transform_all_call(std, A_LOPG(a));
4003 A_LOPP(a, l);
4004 return a;
4005 case A_AGOTO:
4006 case A_ASNGOTO:
4007 return a;
4008 case A_DO:
4009 l1 = transform_all_call(std, A_M1G(a));
4010 l2 = transform_all_call(std, A_M2G(a));
4011 if (A_M3G(a))
4012 l3 = transform_all_call(std, A_M3G(a));
4013 else
4014 l3 = 0;
4015 if (A_M4G(a))
4016 l4 = transform_all_call(std, A_M4G(a));
4017 else
4018 l4 = 0;
4019 A_M1P(a, l1);
4020 A_M2P(a, l2);
4021 A_M3P(a, l3);
4022 A_M4P(a, l4);
4023 return a;
4024 case A_DOWHILE:
4025 l = transform_all_call(std, A_IFEXPRG(a));
4026 A_IFEXPRP(a, l);
4027 return a;
4028 case A_ENDDO:
4029 case A_CONTINUE:
4030 case A_END:
4031 case A_ENTRY:

4033 case A_ICALL:
4034 case A_CALL:
4035 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(a);

4037 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {

4040 ag = _transform_func(std, ARGT_ARG(argt, i));

4045 case A_REDISTRIBUTE:

4048 case A_STOP:
4049 case A_PAUSE:
4050 case A_RETURN:

4052 case A_ALLOC:

4058 interr("transform_all_call: WHERE stmt found", std, 3);
4059 return a;
4060 case A_FORALL:
4061 case A_ENDFORALL:
4062 return a;
4063 case A_COMMENT:
4064 case A_COMSTR:
4065 return a;
4066 case A_LABEL:
4067 return a;
4068 /* expressions */
4069 case A_BINOP:

4071 d = A_DTYPEG(a);
4072 l = transform_all_call(std, A_LOPG(a));
4073 r = transform_all_call(std, A_ROPG(a));

4108 ARGT_ARG(argt, i) = ag;

4111 return a;
4112 case A_FUNC:
4113 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(a);

4116 ag = _transform_func(std, ARGT_ARG(argt, i));
4117 ARGT_ARG(argt, i) = ag;

4121 case A_CNST:

4132 }

4137 case A_TRIPLE:

4142 case A_HOFFSET:
4143 case A_HOWNERPROC:

4156 case A_MASTER:
4157 case A_ENDMASTER:
4158 case A_ATOMIC:
4159 case A_ATOMICCAPTURE:
4160 case A_ATOMICREAD:
4161 case A_ATOMICWRITE:
4162 case A_ENDATOMIC:
4163 case A_CRITICAL:
4164 case A_ENDCRITICAL:
4165 case A_NOBARRIER:
